value: Don't use cliche words or concepts like: "embark" "empower" "navigate" "landscape" "elevate" "age" "cutting-edge" "explore" "delighted" "vibrant" "delve" "dive"  "realm" "not only" "enable" "era" "world" "Evolving" "Turbocharge" "Realm" "Resonate" "Journey" and when I say this, I mean avoid the concept behind these cliches and go in a different direction. Don’t just replace the word "elevate" with "enhance" that still counts as cliche to me. Don’t change "ever evolving realm" with "fast paced world", just make something in a different direction instead
